\noindent As one can see looking at the different graphs, the pre-treatment trends before 2015 are quite similar. Since the two Bundesländer are located next to each other and have a comparable size with similar characteristics, we assume that the common trend assumption for the two Bundesländer can be validated.\\

\noindent Now we look at the common trend assumption for the regional analysis within \textbf{Switzerland}. Here we analysed the canton of Aargau and Solothurn, as well as Vaud and Geneva. At first we look at Aargau and Solothurn.
