\noindent We again observe that the pre-treatment trends before 2015 are quite similar in the two cantons. Since the two cantons are located right next to each other and therefore have similar demographics and other characteristics. We assume that the common trend assumption can be validated for Aargau and Solothurn.\\

\noindent Now we look as well at the graphs for Vaud and Geneva and see a similar picture.
\begin{figure}[!htb]
    \minipage{0.3\textwidth}
